modules.name: React
modules.comments: This module defines foreign types and functions which wrap React's functionality.

declarations.comments: A virtual DOM node, or component.
declarations.title: ReactElement

declarations.comments: A reference to a component, essentially React's `this`.
declarations.title: ReactThis

declarations.comments: An event handler. The type argument represents the type of the event.
declarations.title: EventHandler

declarations.comments: This phantom type indicates that read access to a resource is allowed.
declarations.title: Read

declarations.comments: This phantom type indicates that write access to a resource is allowed.
declarations.title: Write

declarations.comments: An access synonym which indicates that neither read nor write access are allowed.
declarations.title: Disallowed

declarations.comments: An access synonym which indicates that both read and write access are allowed.
declarations.title: ReadWrite

declarations.comments: An access synonym which indicates that reads are allowed but writes are not.
declarations.title: ReadOnly

declarations.comments:
This effect indicates that a computation may read or write the component state.

The first type argument is a row of access types (`Read`, `Write`).
declarations.title: ReactState

declarations.comments: This effect indicates that a computation may read the component props.
declarations.title: ReactProps

declarations.comments:
This effect indicates that a computation may read the component refs.

The first type argument is a row of access types (`Read`, `Write`).
declarations.title: ReactRefs

declarations.comments: A component will receive props function.
declarations.title: ComponentWillReceiveProps

declarations.comments: Create a component specification with a provided state.
declarations.title: spec

declarations.comments: Create a component specification with a get initial state function.
declarations.title: spec'

declarations.comments: Write the component state with a callback.
declarations.title: writeStateWithCallback

declarations.comments: Transform the component state by applying a function.
declarations.title: transformState

declarations.comments: Create a React class from a specification.
declarations.title: createClass

declarations.comments: Create a stateless React class with children access.
declarations.title: createClassStateless'

declarations.comments: Create an element from a React class spreading the children array. Used when the children are known up front.
declarations.title: createElement

declarations.comments: Create an element from a React class passing the children array. Used for a dynamic array of children.
declarations.title: createElementDynamic

declarations.comments: Create an element from a tag name spreading the children array. Used when the children are known up front.
declarations.title: createElementTagName

declarations.comments: Create an element from a tag name passing the children array. Used for a dynamic array of children.
declarations.title: createElementTagNameDynamic

declarations.comments: Create a factory from a React class.
declarations.title: createFactory
